CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Petition for Guardianship of the Property of Alleged Disabled Person – Stay of
3 Civil Actions and Proceedings
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing a party to the guardianship of the property of an alleged
5 disabled person to request a stay of certain civil actions or proceedings on the filing
6 of a petition for guardianship of the property of an alleged disabled person; requiring
7 a certain party to the guardianship of the property of an alleged disabled person to
8 provide certain notice to a court granting a stay and to parties to a civil action or
9 proceeding; establishing that a stay granted by a court may be in effect only for a
10 certain period of time, subject to a certain exception; requiring a court to
11 automatically lift a stay of certain civil actions under certain circumstances;
12 requiring, to effectuate service of process for certain civil actions against an alleged
13 disabled person, the temporary or permanent guardian of the property of the
14 disabled person to be served; and generally relating to petitions for guardianship of
15 the property of an alleged disabled person.
